{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f970b609-6b91-4bc7-8de8-46f9283b9630","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n### 1. Update packages\n- **Upgrade** `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it adds Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n- **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's the VSTest entry point and no longer needed.\n\n### 2. Enable the new platform\nAdd this to your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Run tests\n- `dotnet test` works as before (with .NET SDK 9.0.200+).\n- You can also run the test executable directly: `./YourTestProject`\n\n### Key notes\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **v5+** ships a Microsoft.Testing.Platform adapter alongside the VSTest one, so the switch is opt-in via the MSBuild property.\n- If you still need VSTest compatibility (e.g., older CI), you can keep both adapters temporarily by leaving `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` in place — but it's not required for the new platform.\n- The `--` separator is used for platform options: `dotnet test -- --help` to see them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3bb91640-7d06-498d-9ec9-e762811bb3d2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":390,"requestId":"BD13:319933:1C91364:2034F8F:6A07C478"},"id":"11602e74-2099-46c4-97d6-ba66046d772c","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:12:34.537Z","parentId":"9482c956-8b9b-46c0-9ca7-555e3fb1d341"}
